#x02013;630) explore options for raising revenue. </p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other3"><title>Indonesia</title><sec><title>Managing acute malnutrition </title><p>Blandina Rosalina Bait et al. (597&#x02013;604) report implementation research from Kupang district.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other4"><title>Japan</title><sec><title>Labour and delivery</title><p>Yuto Maeda et al. (631&#x02013;636) explain shortfalls in analgesia during childbirth.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other5"><title>Thailand</title><sec><title>Meeting national needs</title><p>Sirinad Tiantong et al. (642&#x02013;644) create a new cooperation strategy.</p></sec></sec><sec sec-type="other6"><title>Global</title><sec><title>Deaths before and after 70</title><p>Peter Byass (589&#x02013;596) examines noncommunicable disease mortality correlates.</p></sec><sec><title>Harm reduction for people who inject drugs</title><p>Daniel O&#x02019;Keefe et al. (605&#x02013;611) argue for better indicators of access and impact.</p></sec><sec><title>Emergency care systems</title><p>Taylor W Burkholder et al. (612&#x02013;619) propose a rights-based approach. </p></sec></sec></body></article>